<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd"><html><head><title>CREATE-CHOOSER</title></head><body><div id="bodyContent">	<h3><i>I create a chooser of values for a variable.</i> </h3>	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>	<p><b>CREATE-CHOOSER </b></p>	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>	<pre>create-chooser   &quot;a-b-or-c&quot;<i>&nbsp;; name of global variable</i>  &quot;5&quot; &quot;250&quot;&nbsp;<i>; lower left corner </i>  &quot;80&quot; &quot;300&quot;&nbsp;<i>; upper right corner</i>  &quot;2&quot;&nbsp;<i>; choice selected by default</i>  &quot;a&quot;&nbsp;<i>; choice 0</i>  &quot;b&quot;&nbsp;<i>; choice 1</i>  &quot;c&quot;&nbsp;<i>; choice 2</i>  &quot;2.5&quot;&nbsp;<i>; choice 3</i>  &quot;5&quot;<i>&nbsp;; choice 4</i></pre>	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>	<h2><span class="mw-headline">Variants </span></h2>	<p>All the parameters can be changed. It can also be edited within NetLogo 	but those changes won't be saved. </p>	<h2><span class="mw-headline">Related Micro-behaviours </span></h2>	<p>	<a title="CREATE-PLOT" href="CREATE-PLOT.html">	CREATE-PLOT</a>,	<a title="CREATE-SLIDER" href="CREATE-SLIDER.html">	CREATE-SLIDER</a>,	<a title="CREATE-MONITOR" href="CREATE-MONITOR.html">	CREATE-MONITOR</a> and	<a title="CREATE-BUTTON" href="CREATE-LEFT-TURN-BUTTON.html">	CREATE-LEFT-TURN-BUTTON</a> also create interface elements. </p>	<h2><span class="mw-headline">How this works </span></h2>	<p>This creates a NetLogo chooser for a global variable. In this example the 	variable is named <i>a-b-or-c</i> and the choices are &quot;a&quot;, &quot;b&quot;, or &quot;c&quot;. </p>	<h2><span class="mw-headline">History </span></h2>	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn. </div></body></html>